<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">

<p>This is the 10th year of Śrī Kulottuṅkacōḻatēvar. Today <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>iṉṟu</foreign></supplied> alias <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>āṉa</foreign></supplied> Tiṅkaḷkiḻamai (Monday) and Cataiyam, on the <foreign>aṣṭami</foreign> of <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> the first half of the lunar month <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>pūrvapakṣam</foreign></supplied>, [this is] the order <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>śāsanam</foreign></supplied> of Āticaṇḍeśvara of the temple <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kōyil</foreign></supplied> of Śrī Kaṇṭīśvaramuṭaiyār, the Lord <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>uṭaiyār</foreign></supplied> of big Paḻuvūr <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>periyappaḻuvūr</foreign></supplied> of Uttuṅkatuṅkavaḷanāṭu alias Kuṉṟakkūṟṟam on the northern bank <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaṭakarai</foreign></supplied>; we the executors of temple endowments <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tāṉattōmum</foreign></supplied> of this temple <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ikkōyil</foreign></supplied> and the Śrī Māheśvarars, upon the request <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kēḻviyāl &gt; kēḷviyāl</foreign></supplied> of Pañcavarāyar (the five kings?), Lords <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>uṭaiyār</foreign></supplied> of Ciṟaikkā, chieftains <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>mutalikaḷ</foreign></supplied> who conquered <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>piṭitta</foreign></supplied> this country <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>innāṭu</foreign></supplied>, by the command <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ātēcattāl</foreign></supplied> of Caṇḍeśvara Tēvar, have caused to raise <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eḻuntaruḷivitta</foreign></supplied> <foreign>tirunā <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> varai</foreign> in the temple <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kōyalil &gt; kōyilil</foreign></supplied> of Tiruttōṟṟamuṭaiyār, the lord <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>uṭaiyār</foreign></supplied> of this town <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ivvūr</foreign></supplied>, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> of this town <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ivvūr</foreign></supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> </p></div>

